This repository is decision-driven.

Before changing code, read ADRs first.

Minimum reading order:
1. docs/adr/README.md
2. docs/rules/README.md (non-negotiable constraints)
3. docs/guidelines/README.md (active conventions)
4. docs/glossary/README.md (domain terms)
5. docs/runbook/ (only for operational tasks)
6. Relevant ADRs

Do not change architecture before checking ADRs.

If a new convention emerges, draft a guideline.
If a non-negotiable constraint emerges, draft a rule.
If an operational procedure is missing, draft a runbook.
If a new architectural choice appears, draft a new ADR.

